{{Quote|One of these Great Schisms occured approximately seven thousand years ago, when a group of Dark Jedi discovered that they could use the Force to transform creatures into mutant warriors, mounts, and spirit-devouring Leviathans.|[[Vodo-Siosk Baas]]|<ref name="jvs" />}}
The '''Second Great Schism''' was a [[Great Schism/Legends|divisive split]] among the ranks of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] that occurred in the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[7003 BBY]]. [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] who practiced [[Sith alchemy/Legends|alchemy]] and the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side of the Force]] as [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] broke from the Jedi Order, and the war known as the [[Hundred-Year Darkness/Legends|Hundred-Year Darkness]] followed in [[7000 BBY]].<ref name="jvs" />

{{Event-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|While the details are lost in the mists of time, Galactic historians believe there has been a rift between the light side and the dark side of the Force almost since the foundation of the Jedi Order some 25,000 standard years before the Battle of Yavin. Many think it was one rogue Jedi who fell to the dark side, turned others, and eventually built an entire army of dark siders. For the next century, a deadly war swept the galaxy, destroying planets and civilizations before the Jedi Knights prevailed.|[[Stephen J. Sansweet]]|<ref name="Ask">{{SWArchive|url=community/askjc/steve/askjc20000619.html|text=Ask the Lucasfilm Jedi Council - June 19, 2000}}</ref>}}
The first reference to fallen Jedi becoming the rulers of the "Sith civilization" to be published was in [[Tales of the Jedi – The Freedon Nadd Uprising 1|''Tales of the Jedi – The Freedon Nadd Uprising'' 1]].<ref name="TFU">[[Tales of the Jedi – The Freedon Nadd Uprising 1|''Tales of the Jedi – The Freedon Nadd Uprising'' 1]]</ref> This information was again mentioned in [[Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith 1|''Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith'' 1]].<ref name="DLOTS1">[[Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith 1|''Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith'' 1]]</ref> [[Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith 3|''Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith'' 3]] mentions "the [[Hundred-Year Darkness/Legends|Hundred-Year Darkness]]" in a list of events involving the Dark Side. No further information about it was mentioned.<ref name="DLOTS3">[[Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith 3|''Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith'' 3]]</ref>

In the [[Star Wars comic books|comic]] book [[Tales of the Jedi – The Golden Age of the Sith 0|''Tales of the Jedi -'' ''The Golden Age of the Sith'' 0]], published on [[July 31]], [[1996]]<ref name="Marvel">{{Marvel|url=comics/issue/54589/star_wars_tales_of_the_jedi_-_the_golden_age_of_the_sith_1996|text=Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi - The Golden Age of the Sith (1996)}}</ref> by [[Dark Horse Comics]],<ref name="DarkHorse">{{DarkHorse|url=Comics/95-416/Star-Wars-Tales-of-the-Jedi---The-Golden-Age-of-the-Sith-0-of-5|text=Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi - The Golden Age of the Sith #0 (of 5)}}</ref> a young [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]], [[Odan-Urr/Legends|Odan-Urr]], conveys tales of the Sith to [[Ooroo/Legends|Master Ooroo]], recounting that "[[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]]" of "the [[First Great Schism]] of the Jedi Knights"  were "defeated after a century of bloodshed" and that "[[Exiles|Jedi Exiles]]", noted as such in the text of issue 0, subsequently "forged the [[Sith Empire (Pre-Republic)|Sith civilization]] into a [[Sith Empire/Legends|new empire]] ".<ref name="GAS0">[[Tales of the Jedi – The Golden Age of the Sith 0|''Tales of the Jedi – The Golden Age of the Sith'' 0]]</ref> In [[1996]]'s [[Tales of the Jedi – The Golden Age of the Sith 2|''Tales of the Jedi'' – ''The Golden Age of the Sith'' 2]], the [[Force ghost/Legends|ghost]] of [[Marka Ragnos]] recounts how this "Great Schism between the Dark Side and the Light turned Jedi against Jedi." Ragnos goes on to say that it has been "many centuries" since then. In the same issue, Odan-Urr tells [[Teta/Legends|Teta]] that "it has been many centuries" since "evil Jedi" were "banished".<ref name="TOTJ 2">[[Tales of the Jedi – The Golden Age of the Sith 2|''Tales of the Jedi – The Golden Age of the Sith'' 2]]</ref> In [[Tales of the Jedi – The Golden Age of the Sith 4|''Tales of the Jedi'' – ''The Golden Age of the Sith'' 4]], Odan-Urr warns the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Galactic Senate]] about "exiled Jedi, defeated millennia ago".<ref name="TOTJ 4">[[Tales of the Jedi – The Golden Age of the Sith 4|''Tales of the Jedi – The Golden Age of the Sith'' 4]]</ref>

''[[The Essential Chronology (real-world book)|The Essential Chronology]]'' ([[2000]]), described "a century of bloodshed" associated with "the first great schism within the Jedi Knights" "millennia" and "centuries" before the [[Great Hyperspace War/Legends|Great Hyperspace War]].<ref name="TEC">[[The Essential Chronology (real-world book)|''The Essential Chronology'']]</ref>

Elaborating on comments made by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]] via the [[StarWars.com]]'s ''[[Ask the Lucasfilm Jedi Council]]'' feature in [[2000]],<ref name="Ask" /> ''[[Star Wars: Secrets of the Sith]]'' ([[2000]]), by [[Iain R. Morris]], [[Benjamin Harper|Ben Harper]] and [[Marc Cerasini]], placed the "first uprising of the dark side" and subsequent "century-long battle" somewhere between "25,000-5,000 B.B.Y.", and further described the idea that galactic historians believed that one rogue Jedi Knight was responsible for turning fellow Knights, which then led to the creation of a "fleet of spacecraft" used against the Jedi during the "next hundred years."<ref name="SWSotS">''[[Star Wars: Secrets of the Sith]]''</ref>

[[Arden Lyn]]'s biography in [[Abel G. Peña]]'s "[[The Emperor's Pawns]]", a collection of biographies that were published in [[Star Wars Gamer 5|''Star Wars Gamer'' #5]] ([[2001]]), stated that "Xendor and his minions wreaked havoc during The First Great Schism" while the attached "Adventure Seed: Life After Death", stated that Arden was "twisted after 250 centuries of 'death'" meaning that the First Great Schism took place approximately 25,000 years prior to her reawakening.<ref name="tep">{{GamerCite|5|The Emperor's Pawns}}</ref> On [[June 29]], [[2006]], Abel revealed that he had exorcised portions of his article, "[[Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties]]" pertaining to an unrelated Second Great Schism in [[10,000 BBY]] involving the [[Sorcerers of Tund/Legends|Sorcerers of Tund]].<ref name="JCF">{{JCFCite|url=posts/24255327|board=Literature|thread=Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties|user=[[Abel G. Peña|Halagad_Ventor]]|PTtime=2006-06-29|quote=...I never updated the Sorcerers of Tund section of Evil Never Dies (which originally had them as a group of Jedi schismatics of an intellectually rather than violently motivated Second Great Schism, placed around 10,000 BBY)...|archiveurl=https://boards.theforce.net/threads/evil-never-dies-the-sith-dynasties.24202765/page-9#post-24255327}}</ref>

''[[The Dark Side Sourcebook]]'' ([[2001]]), released only a month after ''The Emperor's Pawns'', did not mention Xendor or Arden Lyn, only describing "the first dark side uprising" that took place "during this ancient period" and that this battle lasted "more than a century" prior to these "Dark Jedi" discovering the Sith.<ref name="TDSSB">''[[The Dark Side Sourcebook]]''</ref>

The timeline in the beginning of ''[[The New Essential Guide to Characters]]'' ([[2002]]) lists "The First Great Schism between followers of the dark side and the light side occurs. After more than a century, the dark-siders are driven off into the wilds of the galaxy" under the heading "circa [[25,000 BBY/Legends|25,000 B.B.Y.]]" while also listing the "The Jedi Knights lead the Republic through the Hundred-Year Darkness" under the heading of "circa [[7000 BBY|7,000 B.B.Y.]]"<ref name="NEGC">''[[The New Essential Guide to Characters]]''</ref>

[[Naga Sadow/Legends|Naga Sadow]]'s biography in ''The New Essential Guide to Characters'' says, "The First Great Schism between the light and dark sides of the Force occured in the early years of the Old Republic. Certain Jedi turned to the dark side, and when defeated, they fled the civilized galaxy and conquered a primitive species-the Sith. They made themselves the Lords of the Sith, and named the greatest among them the Dark Lord. Naga Sadow, heir to this wicked tradition, became the first Sith Lord in nearly twenty millennia to reestablish contact with the forgotten Republic".<ref name="NEGC" />

''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' ([[2005]]) reasserted that the Hundred-Year Darkness occured ~7000 BBY, but also revealed it to be the same event as the "century of bloodshed" mentioned in ''Tales of the Jedi: Golden Age of the Sith'' and to now follow a "Second Great Schism" while the "First Great Schism" was [[Retroactive continuity|retconned]] to be a separate event.<ref name="NEC" /> In spite of this retcon, ''[[Star Wars: The Ultimate Visual Guide: Special Edition]]'', which was published in [[May]] [[2007]],<ref name="SDate">{{DK|host=dorlingkindersley-uk.co.uk|url=nf/Book/BookDisplay/0,,9781405318686,00.html|text=Star Wars the Ultimate Visual Guide|nolive=1}}</ref> and ''[[Star Wars: The Ultimate Visual Guide: Updated and Expanded]]'', which was published on [[April 30]], [[2012]],<ref name="UDate">{{DK|subdomain=us|url=nf/Book/BookDisplay/0,,9780756692483,00.html|text=Star Wars: The Ultimate Visual Guide: Updated and Expanded|nolive=1}}</ref> say that the Exiles turned to the dark side "in the early years of the Old Republic."<ref name="UVGSE">''[[Star Wars: The Ultimate Visual Guide: Special Edition]]''</ref><ref name="UVGUE">''[[Star Wars: The Ultimate Visual Guide: Updated and Expanded]]''</ref>

When asked about this retcon, [[Daniel Wallace]], author of ''The New Esssential Chronology'', said it was because of "LFL internal documents" dating Dark Jedi contact with the [[Sith (species)/Legends|Sith species]] at ~7000 BBY.<ref name="NECt">{{Blogspot|subdomain=geekosity|url=2005/10/new-essential-chronology-talkback.html|name=Daniel Wallace's Geekosity|text=The New Essential Chronology: Talkback thread}}</ref> On [[January 11]], 2006, [[Leland Chee]] said that this retcon was to "correct the the [sic] original discrepency of the timing of the Great Schism introduced by ''The New Essential Guide to Characters''."<ref name="Leland Chee">{{SWBoards|url=thread.jspa?threadID=152583&start=630|thread=Holocron continuity database questions|user=[[Leland Chee|Tasty Taste]]|date=2006-01-11|time=04:12 PM}}</ref> On [[June 30]], 2006, Abel G. Peña stated that he "didn't quite understand this realignment of the origins of the Sith."<ref name="JCFAbel">{{JCFCite|url=posts/24263085|board=Literature|thread=Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties|user=[[Abel G. Peña|Halagad_Ventor]]|PTtime=2006-06-29|quote=I didn't quite understand this realignment of the origins of the Sith either, but at least for now it is what it is.|archiveurl=https://boards.theforce.net/threads/evil-never-dies-the-sith-dynasties.24202765/page-10#post-24263085}}</ref>

